    <att name="summary">The Pacific Ecosystem Autonomous Research Laboratory (PEARL) at the Bamfield Marine Sciences Centre has been a site for shore-based and high-resolution measurement of surface seawater CO2 content since August 2025. Measurements of in situ temperature, salinity, and CO2 partial pressure are made near-continuously on seawater drawn from a sample line with an intake 15 m from shore and a depth of 1 m in Barkley Sound on the west coast of Vancouver Island. The effort to collect these data are part of the Hakai Institute&#8217;s mission to advance the understanding of carbon cycling in northeast Pacific coastal settings with specific emphasis on ocean acidification. This data contribution consists of provisional measurements spanning the current year.</att>
